  "instructions": [
    "Marinate the jumbo shrimp in a blend of coconut oil, lime juice, fish sauce, soy sauce, honey, brown sugar, grated ginger, garlic, smoked paprika, and black pepper for at least 30 minutes.",
    "Preheat the tandoor to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Thread the marinated shrimp onto the bamboo skewers, leaving a 1-inch space between each shrimp.",
    "Grill the shrimp in the preheated tandoor for 2-3 minutes per side, or until pink and cooked through.",
    "Serve the shrimp hot with your favorite dipping sauce, such as peanut sauce or sambal.",
    "Garnish with fresh cilantro and a squeeze of lime juice, if desired."
